  "description": "This dinner keeps the palate warm and savory while leaning on vegetables and lentils more than fat. Vegetable Kozhukattai in Coconut Broth brings a distinct structure, seasoning pattern, and grain-legume balance to the table.",
  "preparation": "",
  "cooking_steps": [
    "Steam the shaped dumplings on medium heat for 10 minutes until firm and matte.",
    "In a pot, warm oil and saute ginger, chilli, curry leaves, and the vegetable for 2 minutes on medium heat.",
    "Add cooked moong dal, water, coconut milk, and salt and simmer on low heat for 5 minutes.",
    "Slide in the steamed dumplings and cook 2 minutes more so they absorb some broth before serving."
  ],
